# Alfred State College to host 2014 SUNYAC Men’s and Women’s Swimming and Diving Championships

The 2014 State University of New York Athletic Conference (SUNYAC) Men’s and Women’s Swimming and Diving Championships will be held at Alfred State College’s Orvis Activities Center pool from Wednesday, Feb. 19 through Saturday, Feb. 22.

The 2014 State University of New York Athletic Conference (SUNYAC) Men’s and Women’s Swimming and Diving Championships will be held at Alfred State College’s Orvis Activities Center pool from Wednesday, Feb. 19 through Saturday, Feb. 22.

The four-day event will feature 10 SUNYAC schools, including Alfred State, Buffalo State, Brockport, Cortland, Fredonia, Geneseo, New Paltz, Oneonta, Oswego, and Potsdam. The competition will begin at 10 a.m. each day, with finals starting at 6 p.m. Wednesday through Friday, and at 5 p.m. on Saturday.

“We are very excited to be hosting the SUNYAC Swimming and Diving Championships,” said Alfred State Director of Athletics Daryl Arroyo. “This is a great opportunity for our campus and community to showcase our outstanding facilities and our commitment to excellence. We look forward to welcoming the SUNYAC swimming and diving community to Alfred.”

The Orvis Activities Center pool is a six-lane, 25-yard facility that was built in 2002. The pool features a Colorado timing system, which is the same system used at the NCAA Championships. The facility also includes a separate diving well with one- and three-meter boards.

“We are very excited to be hosting the SUNYAC Swimming and Diving Championships,” said Alfred State head coach R.C. Weston. “This is a great opportunity for our campus and community to showcase our outstanding facilities and our commitment to excellence. We look forward to welcoming the SUNYAC swimming and diving community to Alfred.”

The SUNYAC Swimming and Diving Championships will be the first conference championship hosted by Alfred State since the college became a full member of the conference in July 2013. The Pioneers will be competing in their first SUNYAC Championship as a full member.

For more information on the 2014 SUNYAC Swimming and Diving Championships, including a full schedule of events, ticket information, and more, visit http://www.alfredstateathletics.com/sports/2013/12/3/SUNYAC%20Swim%20Dive%20Championships.aspx.

**Summary of the 2014 SUNYAC Swimming and Diving Championships at Alfred State:**

- **Dates:** February 19–22, 2014  
- **Location:** Orvis Activities Center Pool, Alfred State College  
- **Schedule:**  
  - **Daily Events:** 10:00 AM (prelims)  
  - **Finals:** 6:00 PM (Wednesday–Friday), 5:00 PM (Saturday)  
- **Participating Schools:** 10 SUNYAC institutions (Alfred State, Buffalo State, Brockport, Cortland, Fredonia, Geneseo, New Paltz, Oneonta, Oswego, Potsdam).  
- **Facilities:**  
  - 25-yard, six-lane pool with a Colorado timing system (used at NCAA Championships).  
  - Separate diving well with 1m and 3m boards.  
- **Significance:** First SUNYAC championship hosted by Alfred State since becoming a full conference member in July 2013.  

**Quotes from Officials:**  
- **Daryl Arroyo (Director of Athletics):** Highlighted pride in showcasing facilities and community.  
- **R.C. Weston (Head Coach):** Emphasized commitment to excellence and welcoming the swimming/diving community.
